Class LocateNodeCommand

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.mobius.vdrapi.command.PromptingCommandBase
        |
        +--com.mobius.vdrapi.command.LocateNodeCommand
All Implemented Interfaces:
ICanPromptForKeyValue, ICommand, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedObjectWithNode, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold, INeedPromptForKeyValue
public class LocateNodeCommand
extends com.mobius.vdrapi.command.PromptingCommandBase
implements INeedObjectWithNode, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold

This command object locates a node in the topic or report hierarchy.

It has the following parameters:

  • DOCUMENTSERVER "xxxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the document server to connect to. If the document server needs prompting for a user ID or password, the LocateNodeCommand calls IHasLoginCredentials. This is only necessary if other parameters specified require an active connection to the server.

    A document server's default trace threshold level (message logging) is set to ViewDirectSeverityLevel.SL_DISASTER, the minimum tracing level. To change the document server's trace threshold level, implement the IHasTraceThreshold interface, and assign the object to this command via setObjectWithTraceThreshold(IHasTraceThreshold traceThreshold).

  • FAILNOMATCH - this optional flag parameter specifies that when searching, the LocateNodeCommand should not return the last item in the list by default. Instead, it throws a DataNotFoundException, in cases where the search parameter is past the end of the list.

  • EXACTMATCH - this optional flag parameter specifies that when searching, the LocateNodeCommand should return only the item searched for, if found. Otherwise, it throws a DataNotFoundException.

  • RETURNLAST - this optional flag parameter specifies that when searching, the LocateNodeCommand should always return the last item in the list. If this flag, FAILNOMATCH, or EXACTMATCH are not specified, this is the default behavior. NOTE: FAILNOMATCH, EXACTMATCH, and RETURNLAST are mutually exclusive. Providing more than one of these parameters will result in a KeyInvalidException being thrown.

  • LOCATETOPICITEMENTRY - this optional flag parameter specifies that when navigating beyond the TopicVersion level of the Topic hierarchy, the LocateNodeCommand should traverse the TopicItemEntry hierarchy rather than the TopicItem hierarchy. This flag may only be specified if the topic, topic version, topic item, topic report, topic report version, and topic section RBA parameters are all specified. If it is specified when any of these items are missing, an exception is thrown. Refer to TopicVersionNode.and TopicItemEntryNode for more information.

  • REPORTID "xxxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Report ID to find. If this key or any other report key is passed, topic keys cannot be passed.

  • VERSIONID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Report Version ID to find. The format is YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.

  • SECTIONID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Report Section ID to find.

  • PAGE "xx" - this optional parameter specifies which page of the section to find.

  • TOPICID "xxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Topic ID to find. If this key or any other topic key is passed, report keys cannot be passed.

  • TOPICVERSION "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the topic version to find. The format is YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.

  • TOPICITEM "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the topic item to find.

  • TOPICREPORT "xxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the topic item report to find.

  • TOPICREPORTVERSION "xxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the topic item report version to find. The format is YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.

  • TOPICSECTIONRBA "xxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the section page RBA. This is usually returned from a topic section. If you have an INode Topic Section, you can request that key value, which should be an RBA.

  • TOPICPAGE "xxx" - this optional parameter specifies the topic item report section page number.
The locate command navigates down the node tree until it reaches the last optional parameter. For example, if the following command was created, the node returned is page 4 or the last page in the first section) of Report AC001: 
LOCATENODE DOCUMENTSERVER "Bob's Server" REPORT 'AC001' PAGE 4

Note:
  • The LocateNodeCommand implements the INeedLoginCredentials and INeedFullLoginCredentials interfaces. However, the caller must choose either IHasLoginCredential or IHasFullLoginCredentials but not both. If both interfaces are implemented, the command throws a MultipleCallbacksSetException.

  • If the caller implements the IHoldSession interface, neither IHasLoginCredentials nor IHasFullLoginCredentials is required.

setObjectWithSession

public void setObjectWithSession(IHoldSession objectWithSession)
Sets the callback object.

Under normal circumstances, the LocateNode command creates its own session internally, which it then uses to perform its function. This optional callback enables the caller to provide an existing session for the command to use, rather than requiring it to create its own session. When provided, the session must be connected to the document server specified in the load parameters.

Specified by:
setObjectWithSession in interface INeedObjectWithSession
Parameters:
objectWithSession - object called when this class needs a session.
